---
import ToolShell from '../../components/ToolShell.astro';
import ToolResultActions from '../../components/ToolResultActions.astro';
---
<ToolShell title="Google Ads VAT decision guide" metaTitle="Is There VAT on Google Ads? UK & Guernsey Decision Guide" eyebrow="Billing checklist" description="Use billing location, account type and VAT status to identify which Google Ads documents and tax questions to check. Educational, not tax advice.">
  <div slot="hero-card" class="vat-hero"><span>Important</span><strong>Check the payments profile and invoice—not a generic article alone.</strong><p>Google’s contracting entity and tax treatment can depend on account and billing details.</p></div>
  <div slot="tool" class="tool-card"><div class="vat-intro"><span>Three checks</span><h2>Build your billing checklist</h2><p>This does not calculate VAT or replace advice from your accountant.</p></div><form id="vat-guide" class="form-stack">
    <div class="field"><label for="billing-location">Where is the Google Ads payments profile based?</label><select id="billing-location" name="location" required><option value="">Select location</option><option value="uk">United Kingdom</option><option value="guernsey">Guernsey / Channel Islands</option><option value="eu">European Union</option><option value="other">Another country</option></select></div>
    <div class="field"><label for="account-purpose">How is the account used?</label><select id="account-purpose" name="purpose" required><option value="">Select account use</option><option value="business">Business / organisation advertising</option><option value="personal">Personal or non-business use</option><option value="unsure">Not sure how the payments profile is classified</option></select></div>
    <div class="field"><label for="vat-status">Is the organisation VAT registered in the UK?</label><select id="vat-status" name="vatStatus" required><option value="">Select status</option><option value="yes">Yes</option><option value="no">No</option><option value="na">Not applicable / outside the UK</option><option value="unsure">Not sure</option></select></div>
    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Show the checks to make</button>
  </form><div class="result-panel" id="vat-results" aria-live="polite"><div class="vat-result-head"><span>Decision checklist</span><h2 id="vat-heading">—</h2></div><div class="vat-answer" id="vat-answer"></div><ol class="vat-checks" id="vat-checks"></ol><div class="source-box"><strong>Use the primary sources</strong><a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/2375370?hl=en-GB" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads: taxes in your country ↗</a><a href="https://www.gov.uk/vat-on-services-from-abroad" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HMRC: VAT on services from abroad ↗</a><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/vat-place-of-supply-of-services-notice-741a" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HMRC VAT Notice 741A ↗</a></div><ToolResultActions toolName="google_ads_vat_guide" resultId="vat-results" resultTitle="Google Ads VAT decision checklist" /><p class="disclaimer"><strong>Not tax advice:</strong> tax treatment depends on the exact contracting entity, billing address, account classification and your circumstances. Confirm the treatment with your accountant, tax adviser or relevant authority before filing a return.</p></div></div>
  <h2>Why Google Ads VAT answers differ</h2><p>Google Ads tax treatment depends on the payments profile, country, account type and the Google entity serving the account. Google’s own guidance says business customers may need to self-assess VAT and should confirm the position with their tax authority or adviser.</p>
  <h2>UK businesses receiving services from abroad</h2><p>HMRC explains that the reverse charge can apply when a UK business receives services from a non-UK supplier. Where it applies, the recipient accounts for the VAT as if it were both supplier and customer. Partial exemption and registration circumstances can change the practical outcome.</p>
  <h2>Guernsey and the Channel Islands</h2><p>HMRC VAT Notice 741A states that the Channel Islands are outside the UK for VAT purposes. That does not make every tax question disappear: confirm the payments profile location, contracting entity, invoice and any local obligations relevant to your organisation.</p>
  <h2>Documents to keep</h2><ul><li>The monthly invoice or statement downloaded from Google Ads billing.</li><li>The payments profile legal name, address, account type and tax details.</li><li>Evidence of the contracting Google entity.</li><li>Your adviser’s treatment and any reverse-charge working used in the return.</li></ul>
</ToolShell>
<script>
  const vatForm=document.getElementById('vat-guide');
  vatForm?.addEventListener('submit',event=>{event.preventDefault();const data=new FormData(vatForm);const location=data.get('location'),purpose=data.get('purpose'),status=data.get('vatStatus');let heading='',answer='',checks=[];
    if(location==='uk'&&purpose==='business'&&status==='yes'){heading='A reverse-charge review is likely to be relevant';answer='A UK VAT-registered business buying advertising services from a non-UK Google entity may need to account for VAT using the reverse charge. Do not assume “no VAT charged” means “nothing to report”.';checks=['Download the invoice and identify the supplying Google entity.','Confirm the payments profile is classified for business use and contains the correct VAT number.','Ask your accountant whether the reverse charge applies and how it should appear in the VAT return.','Check whether partial exemption limits recovery of input tax.'];}
    else if(location==='uk'&&purpose==='business'){heading='Check the invoice and VAT-registration implications';answer='Business use and a UK billing location can create different treatment from a personal account. If VAT is not charged, do not assume the position is settled—especially if the business is not VAT registered.';checks=['Identify the supplying Google entity on the invoice.','Confirm the payments profile account type and legal address.','Ask an adviser whether services received from abroad affect the business’s VAT obligations or registration position.','Keep the monthly statement and the advice supporting the treatment.'];}
    else if(location==='uk'&&purpose==='personal'){heading='The account may be treated as a UK non-business customer';answer='Google’s tax guidance indicates that tax treatment changes with account type and country. Review the actual transaction and payments profile to see whether UK VAT has been charged.';checks=['Check the account type in the Google payments profile.','Download the invoice or monthly statement and identify any VAT line.','Confirm that “personal” accurately reflects the use of the advertising.','Speak to an adviser if the advertising supports any business activity.'];}
    else if(location==='guernsey'){heading='Guernsey is outside the UK VAT system';answer='HMRC states that the Channel Islands are outside the UK for VAT purposes. Google’s invoice treatment still depends on the billing profile and serving entity, so verify the actual document and local circumstances.';checks=['Confirm the payments profile shows the correct Guernsey address and legal entity.','Identify the contracting Google entity and any tax shown on the invoice.','Do not use UK VAT-return guidance unless the organisation also has a relevant UK establishment or obligation.','Confirm any local tax or accounting treatment with a Guernsey adviser.'];}
    else if(location==='eu'){heading='Use the rules for the specific EU member state';answer='Business customers may need to self-assess VAT under the local rules, while account type and VAT ID affect Google’s treatment. This guide cannot determine the member-state filing position.';checks=['Check the Google contracting entity and VAT details.','Validate the VAT ID in the payments profile.','Use the tax authority guidance for the member state.','Confirm self-assessment and invoice treatment with a local adviser.'];}
    else{heading='The billing country’s rules control the next step';answer='Google applies country- and account-specific tax treatment. Use the payments profile and invoice to find the relevant facts before relying on general guidance.';checks=['Confirm billing country, legal name and account type.','Identify the supplying Google entity.','Read Google’s country-specific tax section.','Confirm the treatment with the relevant local authority or adviser.'];}
    document.getElementById('vat-heading').textContent=heading;document.getElementById('vat-answer').textContent=answer;document.getElementById('vat-checks').innerHTML=checks.map(item=>`<li>${item}</li>`).join('');const results=document.getElementById('vat-results');results.dataset.resultSummary=['Spires Digital — Google Ads VAT decision checklist',heading,answer,'Checks to make:',...checks.map((item,index)=>`${index+1}. ${item}`),'Not tax advice. Confirm the treatment with an accountant, tax adviser or relevant authority.'].join('\n');results.classList.add('active');results.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'});window.trackSpiresEvent?.('tool_complete',{tool_name:'google_ads_vat_guide',result_type:String(location)});
  });
</script>
<style>.vat-hero>span,.vat-intro>span{color:#91eadb;font-size:.68rem;font-weight:800;text-transform:uppercase}.vat-hero strong{display:block;margin:.8rem 0;color:white;font-size:1.35rem}.vat-hero p{color:#cbd2df;font-size:.78rem}.vat-intro{margin-bottom:1.5rem}.vat-intro>span{color:var(--violet-dark)}.vat-intro h2{margin:.3rem 0}.vat-intro p{color:var(--slate);font-size:.8rem}.result-panel{background:#fff8eb;border-color:#f0d8aa}.vat-result-head>span{color:#986413;font-size:.68rem;font-weight:800;text-transform:uppercase}.vat-result-head h2{margin:.35rem 0 1rem;font-size:1.6rem}.vat-answer{padding:1rem;border-radius:9px;background:white;color:var(--ink)}.vat-checks{display:grid;gap:.55rem;margin:1rem 0;padding-left:1.4rem;color:var(--slate)}.source-box{display:grid;gap:.5rem;padding:1rem;border-radius:9px;background:var(--ink)}.source-box strong{color:white}.source-box a{color:#91eadb;font-size:.76rem;font-weight:700}.disclaimer{margin-top:1rem;color:#765629}</style>
